DataElement.preferredName: Biospecimen Search Criteria External Identifier java.lang.StringArray
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products.:An object that exists for defining the search parameters for a domain._Happening or arising or located outside or beyond some limits, or especially, some surface.:One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is an array of strings.
